# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "A week, maybe more, had passed. Sarah was no longer entirely certain."
    new "A week, maybe more, had passed. Sarah was no longer entirely certain."

    old "Time appeared to move strangely within the house, or at the very least, the long hours spend studying and practicing made it hard to keep track."
    new "Time appeared to move strangely within the house, or at the very least, the long hours spend studying and practicing made it hard to keep track."

    old "Most every day passed the same."
    new "Most every day passed the same."

    old "Xan was an excellent instructor, but he showed her little mercy. Always pressing her, always demanding more."
    new "Xan was an excellent instructor, but he showed her little mercy. Always pressing her, always demanding more."

    old "Someone else might have complained, but Sarah knew that this was what she had asked for."
    new "Someone else might have complained, but Sarah knew that this was what she had asked for."

    old "She had wanted to go fast, learn as much as she could, and that would demand more of her than she had ever been asked to offer up."
    new "She had wanted to go fast, learn as much as she could, and that would demand more of her than she had ever been asked to offer up."

    old "Books turned to piles, and piles grew into mountains, as she devoured one after the other."
    new "Books turned to piles, and piles grew into mountains, as she devoured one after the other."

    old "The magical arts, outside of inherent ability, also demanded a studious and attentive mind."
    new "The magical arts, outside of inherent ability, also demanded a studious and attentive mind."

    old "You need to move the hand diagonally, and stretch the palm backwards."
    new "You need to move the hand diagonally, and stretch the palm backwards."

    old "Sarah attempted the movement again."
    new "Sarah attempted the movement again."

    old "No, not like that, like this."
    new "No, not like that, like this."

    old "Xan demonstrated the movement again. By now he must have done it over a hundred times."
    new "Xan demonstrated the movement again. By now he must have done it over a hundred times."

    old "Sarah did her best to imitate his every gesture."
    new "Sarah did her best to imitate his every gesture."

    old "Magic, Sarah had come to learn, was a nuanced art of which her latent abilities formed on a miniscule part."
    new "Magic, Sarah had come to learn, was a nuanced art of which her latent abilities formed on a miniscule part."

    old "It was about sensing the energies around herself, those that resided within, learning to seize them, bend them, reshape them."
    new "It was about sensing the energies around herself, those that resided within, learning to seize them, bend them, reshape them."

    old "Then, upon the reshaped essence, imprint a will or a meaning, expressed in word, thought and movement."
    new "Then, upon the reshaped essence, imprint a will or a meaning, expressed in word, thought and movement."

    old "Each element needed to be performed in conjunction and to perfection."
    new "Each element needed to be performed in conjunction and to perfection."

    old "Essence, shape, movement, imprint, utterance."
    new "Essence, shape, movement, imprint, utterance."

    old "When she watched Xan perform his magics, it seemed to her easy and obvious, but whenever she attempted it, the parts never seemed to come together."
    new "When she watched Xan perform his magics, it seemed to her easy and obvious, but whenever she attempted it, the parts never seemed to come together."

    old "Sooner or later, one element of the mix would slip up. Then she tried again, focussing too much on what went wrong, and then the other parts would slip."
    new "Sooner or later, one element of the mix would slip up. Then she tried again, focussing too much on what went wrong, and then the other parts would slip."

    old "After more than a week the only spell she had managed was producing a soft glowing light from her palms."
    new "After more than a week the only spell she had managed was producing a soft glowing light from her palms."

    old "Great, Sarah had reasoned, I can be a living candle if this never works out."
    new "Great, Sarah had reasoned, I can be a living candle if this never works out."

    old "Still, Xan had complimented her, told her that some mages needed months to produce that spell."
    new "Still, Xan had complimented her, told her that some mages needed months to produce that spell."

    old "It was one of Sarah's constant fears, going slow."
    new "It was one of Sarah's constant fears, going slow."

    old "The day's lesson had neared its end."
    new "The day's lesson had neared its end."

    old "Sarah leaned against the wall. She felt the day's lessons drone on and on in her head. She wanted something else to think about."
    new "Sarah leaned against the wall. She felt the day's lessons drone on and on in her head. She wanted something else to think about."

    old "Xan was busy sorting through the pile of books on his desk."
    new "Xan was busy sorting through the pile of books on his desk."

    old "I've been wondering for a while now. This house...it's odd, isn't it?"
    new "I've been wondering for a while now. This house...it's odd, isn't it?"

    old "Odd how?"
    new "Odd how?"

    old "I mean, if a person walks past the front of it, you'd imagine it has maybe five rooms, but there are many more here. I keep discovering new ones, almost every day."
    new "I mean, if a person walks past the front of it, you'd imagine it has maybe five rooms, but there are many more here. I keep discovering new ones, almost every day."

    old "Xan smiled."
    new "Xan smiled."

    old "Yes, it's true that this house does not abide by the rules of the world outside."
    new "Yes, it's true that this house does not abide by the rules of the world outside."

    old "I mean that the house itself is a magical artifact. Endless spells have been woven into it, for all manner of purposes."
    new "I mean that the house itself is a magical artifact. Endless spells have been woven into it, for all manner of purposes."

    old "As a result, the house can adapt itself to the needs of those who inhabit it."
    new "As a result, the house can adapt itself to the needs of those who inhabit it."

    old "You mean it's like a shifting maze?"
    new "You mean it's like a shifting maze?"

    old "Well, not exactly. It shifts and changes based on what we need or imagine we need. Before you came here, the house was very stable."
    new "Well, not exactly. It shifts and changes based on what we need or imagine we need. Before you came here, the house was very stable."

    old "You mean those rooms were never here?"
    new "You mean those rooms were never here?"

    old "Most weren't. The house is attempting to find a balance between your needs and mine. It shifts and adapts. Eventually, I imagine, it will settle on a fixed state."
    new "Most weren't. The house is attempting to find a balance between your needs and mine. It shifts and adapts. Eventually, I imagine, it will settle on a fixed state."

    old "Doesn't that get confusing?"
    new "Doesn't that get confusing?"

    old "Xan shrugged."
    new "Xan shrugged."

    old "Not really. If there is ever something I need, the house provides that as well. A lost book never stays lost for long around here. It always just manages to be where you expect it."
    new "Not really. If there is ever something I need, the house provides that as well. A lost book never stays lost for long around here. It always just manages to be where you expect it."

    old "Sarah struggled to make sense of it. Castle Reinmeer had been the same for centuries, the idea of a living house terrified her in some way."
    new "Sarah struggled to make sense of it. Castle Reinmeer had been the same for centuries, the idea of a living house terrified her in some way."

    old "This is all so strange to get used to..."
    new "This is all so strange to get used to..."

    old "Xan laughed."
    new "Xan laughed."

    old "This is nothing, Sarah. A lot of things you imagine are fixed are maleable in this world."
    new "This is nothing, Sarah. A lot of things you imagine are fixed are maleable in this world."

    old "If you really want to throw your mind for a trip, understand that some doors can even lead to places unconnected to here."
    new "If you really want to throw your mind for a trip, understand that some doors can even lead to places unconnected to here."

    old "Well, there are doors here that can lead to the citadel, to Mythran, to Bagrad. Heck, once I opened a door and I ended up in the Hyral mountains. Can't recommend that one. Orc's aren't very friendly."
    new "Well, there are doors here that can lead to the citadel, to Mythran, to Bagrad. Heck, once I opened a door and I ended up in the Hyral mountains. Can't recommend that one. Orc's aren't very friendly."

    old "Sarah listened intently to Xan, then dared to ask him."
    new "Sarah listened intently to Xan, then dared to ask him."

    old "Is there a door that leads to Rosanna?"
    new "Is there a door that leads to Rosanna?"

    old "Xan pauzed. He put down the books and tried to gather himself."
    new "Xan pauzed. He put down the books and tried to gather himself."

    old "Whatever you're thinking, trust me, you don't want to do that."
    new "Whatever you're thinking, trust me, you don't want to do that."

    old "Sarah could feel tears begin to swell in her eyes."
    new "Sarah could feel tears begin to swell in her eyes."

    old "You just told me that I can walk through a door and see my home country again..."
    new "You just told me that I can walk through a door and see my home country again..."

    old "Now you're telling me not to go?"
    new "Now you're telling me not to go?"

    old "Please...show me where it is. I just want to see my home again."
    new "Please...show me where it is. I just want to see my home again."

    old "Sarah, it won't be like you remember it. The horde has ravaged the country...the capital..."
    new "Sarah, it won't be like you remember it. The horde has ravaged the country...the capital..."

    old "You'll only hurt yourself by going there."
    new "You'll only hurt yourself by going there."

    old "Sarah stared at Xan."
    new "Sarah stared at Xan."

    old "I'm still a princess. It might not mean much in practice, without a kingdom or an army, but I still owe a duty to my people."
    new "I'm still a princess. It might not mean much in practice, without a kingdom or an army, but I still owe a duty to my people."

    old "Xan shook his head."
    new "Xan shook his head."

    old "You're not, Sarah. You're on a path to something different now, something greater."
    new "You're not, Sarah. You're on a path to something different now, something greater."

    old "You can't go through life looking back."
    new "You can't go through life looking back."

    old "Please, Xan, just let me see."
    new "Please, Xan, just let me see."

    old "Xan looked around, perhaps hoping for an escape, but then gave in."
    new "Xan looked around, perhaps hoping for an escape, but then gave in."

    old "Fine, we'll go, but promise me that you will stay close to me, and no matter what, never leave the house."
    new "Fine, we'll go, but promise me that you will stay close to me, and no matter what, never leave the house."

    old "The house?"
    new "The house?"

    old "Yes, the house on the other side. It's warded, but beyond that I can't keep you safe."
    new "Yes, the house on the other side. It's warded, but beyond that I can't keep you safe."

    old "You think I'm so powerful, but I'm just one mage. Even I can't stave off all of Hassar's horde."
    new "You think I'm so powerful, but I'm just one mage. Even I can't stave off all of Hassar's horde."

    old "Xan stormed past her and motioned with his hands for her to keep up."
    new "Xan stormed past her and motioned with his hands for her to keep up."

    old "In only a moment, Sarah found herself standing before a door that had never been where it now was."
    new "In only a moment, Sarah found herself standing before a door that had never been where it now was."

    old "Had she missed it? Or had it only just appeared?"
    new "Had she missed it? Or had it only just appeared?"

    old "Xan grabbed her hand, opened the door, and together the two stepped through."
    new "Xan grabbed her hand, opened the door, and together the two stepped through."

    old "It was night."
    new "It was night."

    old "The cover of darkness made the room hard to make out. Only when Sarah's eyes grew used to the darkness, could she make out the shapes."
    new "The cover of darkness made the room hard to make out. Only when Sarah's eyes grew used to the darkness, could she make out the shapes."

    old "It was different, but not all that much. It seemed like a library, more desks, books, but the style reminded her of the house she had been in only moments earlier."
    new "It was different, but not all that much. It seemed like a library, more desks, books, but the style reminded her of the house she had been in only moments earlier."

    old "It's the same house?"
    new "It's the same house?"

    old "In a way, yes. All one big network of the same house, sprawling across the continents of the world."
    new "In a way, yes. All one big network of the same house, sprawling across the continents of the world."

    old "Easy to get around, easy to leave when things get unpleasant. And it serves as the hub for us to stay informed of the world."
    new "Easy to get around, easy to leave when things get unpleasant. And it serves as the hub for us to stay informed of the world."

    old "The order."
    new "The order."

    old "We keep informed of the movements and changes of the world. Countless apprentices just like you spend their time writing up reports about some revolution here, or a war there."
    new "We keep informed of the movements and changes of the world. Countless apprentices just like you spend their time writing up reports about some revolution here, or a war there."

    old "Then why are mages so rarely mentioned in history?"
    new "Then why are mages so rarely mentioned in history?"

    old "Xan chuckled."
    new "Xan chuckled."

    old "Perceptive. Putting your education to good use I see."
    new "Perceptive. Putting your education to good use I see."

    old "It's simple, we aren't mentioned much because we rarely leave a mark. We observe, we don't intercede."
    new "It's simple, we aren't mentioned much because we rarely leave a mark. We observe, we don't intercede."

    old "There were times when mages tried to affect the world, but our magic, it's too strange for people. It's too unnatural."
    new "There were times when mages tried to affect the world, but our magic, it's too strange for people. It's too unnatural."

    old "Sooner or later, the world turns against us, and there aren't nearly enough of us to put up a fight."
    new "Sooner or later, the world turns against us, and there aren't nearly enough of us to put up a fight."

    old "So we try to pick our fights wisely."
    new "So we try to pick our fights wisely."

    old "Sarah began to lose attention as she noticed soft lights creep into the room from outside."
    new "Sarah began to lose attention as she noticed soft lights creep into the room from outside."

    old "She walked over to the windows and looked outside into the capital. Her city. Her country."
    new "She walked over to the windows and looked outside into the capital. Her city. Her country."

    old "Peering out from the window, Sarah saw the horrors that Xan had hoped to spare her."
    new "Peering out from the window, Sarah saw the horrors that Xan had hoped to spare her."

    old "The house was situated near the city square, dead in the center of the capital. It gave Sarah a good vantage point."
    new "The house was situated near the city square, dead in the center of the capital. It gave Sarah a good vantage point."

    old "Outside, Sarah could see the soldiers of Hassar's army, sprawled out across the square in small groups, campfires in their midsts."
    new "Outside, Sarah could see the soldiers of Hassar's army, sprawled out across the square in small groups, campfires in their midsts."

    old "The soldiers were clearly drunk and loudly enjoying themselves."
    new "The soldiers were clearly drunk and loudly enjoying themselves."

    old "All over the square, Sarah could see the naked bodies wearing collars, mixed in with the soldiers."
    new "All over the square, Sarah could see the naked bodies wearing collars, mixed in with the soldiers."

    old "Her countrymen. Her people. Debased to this."
    new "Her countrymen. Her people. Debased to this."

    old "Most were women, some were men who seemingly came close enough with their soft features for the soldiers not to care."
    new "Most were women, some were men who seemingly came close enough with their soft features for the soldiers not to care."

    old "Out in the open, near the campfires, or off in the shadows, near the edges, all over the square Sarah could see the writhing bodies."
    new "Out in the open, near the campfires, or off in the shadows, near the edges, all over the square Sarah could see the writhing bodies."

    old "Her people, now made slaves, served up their new masters. Serving them their food, their drink and not rarely, offering up their bodies."
    new "Her people, now made slaves, served up their new masters. Serving them their food, their drink and not rarely, offering up their bodies."

    old "None of them seemed to offer up a fight."
    new "None of them seemed to offer up a fight."

    old "It had been weeks, Sarah realized. Weeks since Rosanna fell. Whatever resistance might have existed, had long been stamped out."
    new "It had been weeks, Sarah realized. Weeks since Rosanna fell. Whatever resistance might have existed, had long been stamped out."

    old "Now there were only the countless bodies, performing all manner of service to the soldiers of Hassar's horde."
    new "Now there were only the countless bodies, performing all manner of service to the soldiers of Hassar's horde."

    old "Nearer to her building, Sarah watched as a soldier dragged a woman away from the crowd and pulled her into an alley across from them."
    new "Nearer to her building, Sarah watched as a soldier dragged a woman away from the crowd and pulled her into an alley across from them."

    old "Sarah watched as the soldier pushed the woman up against the wall and grabbed her by the hips."
    new "Sarah watched as the soldier pushed the woman up against the wall and grabbed her by the hips."

    old "He didn't need to use much force, she offered herself up to him with no fight at all."
    new "He didn't need to use much force, she offered herself up to him with no fight at all."

    old "In her blank stare, Sarah could see how she survived. She survived by detaching herself from her condition, in her mind at least."
    new "In her blank stare, Sarah could see how she survived. She survived by detaching herself from her condition, in her mind at least."

    old "Sarah spun around to Xan."
    new "Sarah spun around to Xan."

    old "We need to help her."
    new "We need to help her."

    old "Xan had joined Sarah near the window and watched the same horror play out."
    new "Xan had joined Sarah near the window and watched the same horror play out."

    old "Horrid, the things humans to do one another."
    new "Horrid, the things humans to do one another."

    old "But he made no motion that hinted he would intercede."
    new "But he made no motion that hinted he would intercede."

    old "Xan, you need to do something. You can save her!"
    new "Xan, you need to do something. You can save her!"

    old "Save her? What do you suggest I do, step out and snap my fingers, turn him to ash?"
    new "Save her? What do you suggest I do, step out and snap my fingers, turn him to ash?"

    old "You could!"
    new "You could!"

    old "Yes, and then what?"
    new "Yes, and then what?"

    old "Then the entire square of these degenerates wakes up and attacks me."
    new "Then the entire square of these degenerates wakes up and attacks me."

    old "Sarah looked into Xan's eyes, trying to see what might move him."
    new "Sarah looked into Xan's eyes, trying to see what might move him."

    old "Then you kill all of them! Don't tell me you're not strong enough."
    new "Then you kill all of them! Don't tell me you're not strong enough."

    old "Xan rubbed his temples."
    new "Xan rubbed his temples."

    old "Think, Sarah. Suppose I survive the square, then what? They sound the alarm and soon the entire city garrison will descend on me."
    new "Think, Sarah. Suppose I survive the square, then what? They sound the alarm and soon the entire city garrison will descend on me."

    old "So I can save her?"
    new "So I can save her?"

    old "What about the others, do I save them too? Do I save the entire city?"
    new "What about the others, do I save them too? Do I save the entire city?"

    old "As many as you can!"
    new "As many as you can!"

    old "You're still lost in the girl you were, Sarah. Becoming a mage is more than learning magic. It's also about adopting a greater view of the world."
    new "You're still lost in the girl you were, Sarah. Becoming a mage is more than learning magic. It's also about adopting a greater view of the world."

    old "Do you think what's happening here is unique?"
    new "Do you think what's happening here is unique?"

    old "I've lived a long time, Sarah. I've watched countless cities and nations rise and fall."
    new "I've lived a long time, Sarah. I've watched countless cities and nations rise and fall."

    old "Xan waved his hand at the view."
    new "Xan waved his hand at the view."

    old "Every tragedy you see here has played out countless times before, and it will again. It's just human nature."
    new "Every tragedy you see here has played out countless times before, and it will again. It's just human nature."

    old "I can't stop every tragedy."
    new "I can't stop every tragedy."

    old "But you can stop this one!"
    new "But you can stop this one!"

    old "And why would I stop this one, and not the one before or the one after? What makes these people more special, more deserving of being saved than all the other victims of history?"
    new "And why would I stop this one, and not the one before or the one after? What makes these people more special, more deserving of being saved than all the other victims of history?"

    old "Because they're my people..."
    new "Because they're my people..."

    old "They're not anymore, Sarah. They might have been once, but you're not their princess anymore."
    new "They're not anymore, Sarah. They might have been once, but you're not their princess anymore."

    old "You're going to become so much more. You will rise above this world and see it from the high point. You can't continue to pretend that you're also a part of it."
    new "You're going to become so much more. You will rise above this world and see it from the high point. You can't continue to pretend that you're also a part of it."

    old "If you don't learn that, you'll burn out. You'll try to fix every injustice in the world, and it won't be long before you find yourself outmatched."
    new "If you don't learn that, you'll burn out. You'll try to fix every injustice in the world, and it won't be long before you find yourself outmatched."

    old "Xan seized her by the shoulders."
    new "Xan seized her by the shoulders."

    old "We operate on the scope of the whole world, Sarah. We measure not the years but the centuries. Our duty is towards the whole of the human race."
    new "We operate on the scope of the whole world, Sarah. We measure not the years but the centuries. Our duty is towards the whole of the human race."

    old "We cannot allow ourselves to fail in that greatest of duty, and throw it away because of some random girl, however tragic her circumstance might be."
    new "We cannot allow ourselves to fail in that greatest of duty, and throw it away because of some random girl, however tragic her circumstance might be."

    old "Sarah could see tears form in his eyes."
    new "Sarah could see tears form in his eyes."

    old "It pains me, same it does you. You might not believe it, but I'm human too."
    new "It pains me, same it does you. You might not believe it, but I'm human too."

    old "But we have a great obligation, and we cannot stray from that. We must keep our eyes on the great mission."
    new "But we have a great obligation, and we cannot stray from that. We must keep our eyes on the great mission."

    old "What is that? What is so important that we let this girl suffer?"
    new "What is that? What is so important that we let this girl suffer?"

    old "Xan released her."
    new "Xan released her."

    old "It will come. One day, when you're ready, I will tell you. For now, I only ask that you trust me."
    new "It will come. One day, when you're ready, I will tell you. For now, I only ask that you trust me."

    old "But Sarah had no choice."
    new "But Sarah had no choice."

    old "Xan would not intercede, this she now knew, and she wasn't yet powerful enough to do anything."
    new "Xan would not intercede, this she now knew, and she wasn't yet powerful enough to do anything."

    old "And so the girl suffered her fate, and Sarah turned her eyes away from it."
    new "And so the girl suffered her fate, and Sarah turned her eyes away from it."

    old "The image would remain seared in her mind."
    new "The image would remain seared in her mind."

    old "She never would learn what became of the girl, but her tragedy became a part of Sarah."
    new "She never would learn what became of the girl, but her tragedy became a part of Sarah."

    old "The two returned via the door they came, back to the house in Lethram."
    new "The two returned via the door they came, back to the house in Lethram."

    old "Neither spoke, and each retreated to their rooms, to contemplate in silence."
    new "Neither spoke, and each retreated to their rooms, to contemplate in silence."

